mlisp is a Common Lisp mailing list manager (Smartlist/Mailman 2
replacement) for the panix.com Maildir environment, plus mlisp-bugs,
a Debbugs-compatible email bug tracker built on the same Maildir
architecture.

Features include subscriber self-service, namespace subgroups
(discuss/announce/devel/owner/security/commits/users/distrib/request),
a pluggable pre/post-filter pipeline, GPG signature verification, DMARC
rewriting, VERP bounce attribution, AllFix file distribution, and an
s-expr DSL for procmailrc generation (mlisp-procmail-gen).

Binaries: mlisp, mlisp-admin, mlisp-bugs, mlisp-distrib,
mlisp-procmail-gen.

Home page: https://github.com/denzuko/mlisp
